# Verify builds with cargo check

After changing Rust sources or workspace or crate manifests, run a compile check from the repo root before finishing:

- Default: `cargo check` (or `cargo check -p <crate>` when edits are confined to one workspace member).
- If `CEF_PATH` points at a missing tree and the build fails in `cef-dll-sys`, use `env -u CEF_PATH cargo check` (or match whatever the project `Makefile` / docs use for local checks).

Do not only suggest the command; run it when you have shell access and fix errors the check reports.
